{"bookId": "69048808ef55966cf1d71f1d", "moduleId": "6909cd14d60676ac599cb644", "subjectId": "69075cb049e6141a77a59709", "chapterId": "69075cb149e6141a77a5971b", "subject": "IOQM", "chapter": "Definite Integration", "count": 1, "questions": [{"id": 306336, "subject": "IOQM", "chapter": "Definite Integration", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Olympiad workbook", "q": "What is the greatest integer not exceeding the sum $\\sum_{n=1}^{1599} \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}}$", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "$\\begin{aligned} & \\int_1^{1600} \\frac{d x}{\\sqrt{x}} < \\sum_{n=1}^{1599} \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}} < 1+\\int_1^{1599} \\frac{d x}{\\sqrt{x}} \\\\ & |2 \\sqrt{x}|_1^{1600} < \\sum_{n=1}^{1599} \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}} < 1+|2 \\sqrt{x}|_1^{1599} \\\\ & 78 < \\sum_{n=1}^{1599} \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}} < 2 \\sqrt{1599}-1 \\\\ & 78 < \\sum_{n=1}^{1599} \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}} < 78.97 \\ldots . . \\\\ & \\Rightarrow\\left[\\sum_{n=1}^{1599} \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{n}}\\right]=78\\end{aligned}$", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "Olympiad workbook", "_book": "69048808ef55966cf1d71f1d", "_chapterKey": "69048808ef55966cf1d71f1d__6909cd14d60676ac599cb644__69075cb049e6141a77a59709__69075cb149e6141a77a5971b"}]}